OL,3,CRetail sales boost of 2.5% 'barely
OL,4,Ctouching the sides' of costs, sector
OL,5,Cwarns
OL,7,FLinda Ellett, UK head of consumer,
OL,8,Fretail and leisure markets at KPMG,
OL,9,Fsaid: "The UK's fifth warmest July on
OL,10,FMet Office record brought a boost to
OL,11,Fhome appliance and food and drink
OL,12,Fsales. But rising inflation was also a
OL,13,Fdriver of the latter and monthly non-
OL,14,Ffood sales are only growing at around
OL,15,F1% on average at present.
OL,17,F"With employment costs having risen
OL,18,Fand inflation both a business and
OL,19,Fconsumer side pressure, it remains a
OL,20,Fchallenging trading environment for
OL,21,Fmany retailers."
