OL,3,CRetail sales boost of 2.5% 'barely
OL,4,Ctouching the sides' of costs, sector
OL,5,Cwarns
OL,7,FSeparate figures from Barclays show
OL,8,Fconsumer card spending grew 1.4% year-
OL,9,Fon-year in July ` up from a decline of
OL,10,F0.1% in June ` with discretionary
OL,11,Fspending up 2.4% as changeable weather
OL,12,Fled shoppers to both sunny and rainy
OL,13,Fday activities and items.
OL,15,FBarclays also found clothing
OL,16,Fperforming strongly, up 4.2%, while
OL,17,Fgrowth in online retail spending
OL,18,Fexcluding groceries reached 4.9%, up
OL,19,Ffrom 2.4% in June, as shoppers made
OL,20,Fthe most of discounted items and sales
OL,21,Fevents including Prime Day.
